</taxonomicName>
, Pará, Brazil.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1792,2033]" pageId="2" pageNumber="189">
<emphasis box="[199,280,1792,1817]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="189">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[295,417,1792,1817]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 7–9" captionStart-1="FIGURES 10–11" captionStartId-0="4.[151,264,984,1007]" captionStartId-1="4.[151,264,1780,1803]" captionTargetBox-0="[177,1416,208,940]" captionTargetBox-1="[181,1433,1057,1759]" captionTargetId-0="figure@4.[151,1436,193,964]" captionTargetId-1="figure@4.[151,1436,1057,1759]" captionTargetPageId-0="4" captionTargetPageId-1="4" captionText-0="FIGURES 7–9. H. icterops: BRAZIL: Pará; 7. head, dorsal view; 8. habitus; 9. thorax, dorsal view." captionText-1="FIGURES 10–11. Intersternites. 10. H. icterops: BRAZIL: Pará; structures of the intersternite, in lateral view. Dorsal plate in lateral and ventrolateral views; 11. H. bariai: BRAZIL: Pará; intersternite structures in lateral view." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/2624632/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/2624634/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="189">Figs. 8–10</figureCitation>
). Prothorax yellow, except for weak brownish pigmentation on mediodorsal portion and on both sides of middle lobe; posterior lobe black with yellow margins (
<figureCitation box="[919,1027,1828,1853]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–9" captionStartId="4.[151,264,984,1007]" captionTargetBox="[177,1416,208,940]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,964]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7–9. H. icterops: BRAZIL: Pará; 7. head, dorsal view; 8. habitus; 9. thorax, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2624632/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="189">Figs. 8–9</figureCitation>
); intersternite as large as setifer with a straight carina, a well-developed dorsal plate (triangular in ventrolateral view), lacking a posterior plate (
<figureCitation box="[1340,1423,1864,1889]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1780,1803]" captionTargetBox="[181,1433,1057,1759]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,1057,1759]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10–11. Intersternites. 10. H. icterops: BRAZIL: Pará; structures of the intersternite, in lateral view. Dorsal plate in lateral and ventrolateral views; 11. H. bariai: BRAZIL: Pará; intersternite structures in lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2624634/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="189">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
). Pterothorax with a well-marked thin yellow stripe on medial portion of mesepisternum; remainder of mesepisternum black, except for a pale stripe on its lower portion; mesinfraepisternum pale with a dark stripe on mid portion; mesepimeron black, except for a pale stripe covering its lower 1/3 and almost half of metepisternum; rest of pterothorax pale, except for a small dark stripe at right lower portion of metepimeron (
<figureCitation box="[1197,1265,2008,2033]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–9" captionStartId="4.[151,264,984,1007]" captionTargetBox="[177,1416,208,940]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,964]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7–9. H. icterops: BRAZIL: Pará; 7. head, dorsal view; 8. habitus; 9. thorax, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2624632/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="189">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,392]" pageId="3" pageNumber="190">
<emphasis box="[199,252,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="190">Legs</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[267,335,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–9" captionStartId="4.[151,264,984,1007]" captionTargetBox="[177,1416,208,940]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,964]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7–9. H. icterops: BRAZIL: Pará; 7. head, dorsal view; 8. habitus; 9. thorax, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2624632/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="190">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
). Light brown, with two small dark spots on femora and the first 0.25 of the tibia, remaining areas of legs pale; spines on the femora about the same size as the space between them, subequal in size except for the last two longer spines, numbering seven on profemora and mesofemora and 12 on metafemora; spines on tibiae 
<date box="[1408,1436,224,248]" pageId="3" pageNumber="190">2x</date>
longer than the space between them, except for the last three shorter spines, which decreases in size towards the apex, numbering 11 on protibiae and eight on meso and metatibiae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,392]" pageId="3" pageNumber="190">
<emphasis box="[199,267,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="190">Wings</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[286,373,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1682,1704]" captionTargetBox="[162,1427,1000,1640]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[150,1437,988,1661]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 12. H. icterops: BRAZIL: Pará; fore and hindwings." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2624636/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="190">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
). Px 
<quantity box="[436,497,332,357]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.318" pageId="3" pageNumber="190" unit="in" value="17.0">17 in</quantity>
FW and 
<quantity box="[610,671,332,357]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.064" pageId="3" pageNumber="190" unit="in" value="16.0">16 in</quantity>
HW; hyaline with dark brown venation; pterostigma dark brown, proximal side oblique, overlying almost two cells in FW and two cells in HW.
</paragraph>
