<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1872,2005]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1436,151,933]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="192" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">
<emphasis box="[199,305,1872,1897]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[321,401,1872,1897]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–3" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1694,1717]" captionTargetBox="[355,1205,447,1656]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[340,1247,411,1671]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–3. Ventral view of S8–S10, genital valves and cerci; 1. H. angustipenne, Pastaza, Ecuador; 2. H. bariai, Jatún Sacha, Ecuador; 3. H. icterops, Pará, Brazil." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2624626/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Figs. 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[415,431,1872,1897]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1976,1999]" captionTargetBox="[353,1189,466,1941]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[340,1247,435,1961]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4–6. Lateral view of S8–S10, genital valves and cerci; 4. H. angustipenne, Pastaza, Ecuador; 5. H. bariai, Jatún Sacha, Ecuador; 6. H. icterops, Pará, Brazil." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2624628/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">6</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[444,459,1873,1897]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–9" captionStartId="4.[151,264,984,1007]" captionTargetBox="[177,1416,208,940]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,964]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7–9. H. icterops: BRAZIL: Pará; 7. head, dorsal view; 8. habitus; 9. thorax, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2624632/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">8</figureCitation>
). S1–S3 pale laterally, black dorsally, S2–S3 with black apical rings; S4– 
<geoCoordinate box="[1296,1367,1872,1897]" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="4" pageNumber="191" precision="92" value="-6.008333">S6 0.5</geoCoordinate>
black and 0.5 pale laterally, black dorsally with black apical rings; S7 mostly dark brown with pale coloration laterally; S8–S9 dark brown dorsally, pale laterally; S10 mostly pale, with a dark dorsal area. Genital valves pale, tips at same level as posterior margin of S10; dentition even, row of strong teeth not linear, meeting diagonally at the posterior end, the two apical teeth the largest. Basal portion of styli pale, remainder black. Cerci brown, length approximately 0.8 of S10.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,933]" box="[199,954,223,248]" pageId="5" pageNumber="192">Measurements. Total length 35.7, abdomen 28.3, FW 22.5, HW 22.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,933]" pageId="5" pageNumber="192">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,629,260,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="192">Variation among examined females:</emphasis>
Similar to the described female, except for Px 
<quantity box="[1162,1220,260,285]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.318" pageId="5" pageNumber="192" unit="in" value="17.0">17 in</quantity>
FW and 
<quantity box="[1324,1382,260,285]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.81" pageId="5" pageNumber="192" unit="in" value="15.0">15 in</quantity>
HW in two females, pterostigma overlying 1.5 cell in one female. Total length 33.5–35, abdomen 27.4–27.8, FW 22.4– 22.9, HW 21–22.4.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="192" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,933]" pageId="5" pageNumber="192">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,463,367,392]" pageId="5" pageNumber="192">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1862" box="[471,708,369,392]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="192" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="icterops">
<emphasis box="[471,708,369,392]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="192">Heteragrion icterops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
fits in Lencioni’s Group B. Despite being considered similar to the female of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1886" box="[316,503,405,428]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="192" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angustipenne">
<emphasis box="[316,503,405,428]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="192">H. angustipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, mainly by their coloration patterns (
<bibRefCitation author="Selys-Longchamps, E. de" box="[940,1073,404,429]" pageId="5" pageNumber="192" pagination="233" refId="ref3773" refString="Selys-Longchamps, E. de. (1886) Revision du Synopsis des Agrionines. Premiere partie comprenant les legions Pseudostigma- Podagrion-Platycnemis et Protonevra. Memoires couronnes et autres Memoires, Academie Royale de Belgique, 38 (4), iv + 233." type="journal article" year="1886">Selys 1886</bibRefCitation>
), we consider the female of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1862" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="192" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="icterops">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="192">H. icterops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
closer to 
<taxonomicName box="[359,465,439,464]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="192" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bariai">
<emphasis box="[359,465,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="192">H. bariai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Among the females of Group B occurring in 
<collectingCountry box="[1013,1084,439,464]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="192">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1862" box="[1098,1224,441,464]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="192" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="icterops">
<emphasis box="[1098,1224,441,464]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="192">H. icterops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1285,1391,439,464]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="192" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bariai">
<emphasis box="[1285,1391,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="192">H. bariai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are similar in size (total length 
<quantity box="[465,592,476,501]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.45" metricValueMax="3.6" metricValueMin="3.3" pageId="5" pageNumber="192" unit="mm" value="34.5" valueMax="36.0" valueMin="33.0">33–36 mm</quantity>
), coloration patterns and genital valve morphology, with the single row of teeth not linear and meeting diagonally at the posterior end (
<figureCitation box="[844,954,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–3" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1694,1717]" captionTargetBox="[355,1205,447,1656]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[340,1247,411,1671]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–3. Ventral view of S8–S10, genital valves and cerci; 1. H. angustipenne, Pastaza, Ecuador; 2. H. bariai, Jatún Sacha, Ecuador; 3. H. icterops, Pará, Brazil." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2624626/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="192">Figs. 2–3</figureCitation>
). The main differences between these two species lie in intersternite morphology, and the lack of a posterior plate in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1862" box="[981,1105,549,572]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="192" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="icterops">
<emphasis box="[981,1105,549,572]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="192">H. icterops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1120,1202,548,573]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1780,1803]" captionTargetBox="[181,1433,1057,1759]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,1057,1759]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10–11. Intersternites. 10. H. icterops: BRAZIL: Pará; structures of the intersternite, in lateral view. Dorsal plate in lateral and ventrolateral views; 11. H. bariai: BRAZIL: Pará; intersternite structures in lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2624634/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="192">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
) that is present in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="192" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bariai">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="192">H. bariai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[236,319,583,608]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1780,1803]" captionTargetBox="[181,1433,1057,1759]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,1057,1759]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10–11. Intersternites. 10. H. icterops: BRAZIL: Pará; structures of the intersternite, in lateral view. Dorsal plate in lateral and ventrolateral views; 11. H. bariai: BRAZIL: Pará; intersternite structures in lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2624634/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="192">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
). On the other hand, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1886" box="[563,749,585,608]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="192" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angustipenne">
<emphasis box="[563,749,585,608]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="192">H. angustipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have genital valves long, surpassing the posterior margin of S10 and the single row of teeth almost linear in a parallel arrangement (
<figureCitation box="[947,1024,620,645]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–3" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1694,1717]" captionTargetBox="[355,1205,447,1656]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[340,1247,411,1671]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–3. Ventral view of S8–S10, genital valves and cerci; 1. H. angustipenne, Pastaza, Ecuador; 2. H. bariai, Jatún Sacha, Ecuador; 3. H. icterops, Pará, Brazil." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2624626/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="192">Figs. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1037,1054,620,644]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1976,1999]" captionTargetBox="[353,1189,466,1941]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[340,1247,435,1961]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4–6. Lateral view of S8–S10, genital valves and cerci; 4. H. angustipenne, Pastaza, Ecuador; 5. H. bariai, Jatún Sacha, Ecuador; 6. H. icterops, Pará, Brazil." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2624628/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="192">4</figureCitation>
). Furthermore, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1886" box="[1228,1410,621,644]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="192" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angustipenne">
<emphasis box="[1228,1410,621,644]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="192">H. angustipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is larger in size (total length&gt; 
<quantity box="[464,540,656,680]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="192" unit="mm" value="40.0">40mm</quantity>
), a larger species in comparison to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1862" box="[939,1062,657,680]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="192" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="icterops">
<emphasis box="[939,1062,657,680]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="192">H. icterops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1119,1222,655,680]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="192" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bariai">
<emphasis box="[1119,1222,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="192">H. bariai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Further details on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1886" box="[151,334,693,716]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="192" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angustipenne">
<emphasis box="[151,334,693,716]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="192">H. angustipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
will be treated in a study that is being prepared by Miguel Stand-Pérez, Leon Pérez-Gutiérrez and Cornelio Bota-Sierra (
<emphasis box="[401,538,729,752]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="192">pers. comm.</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="192" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,933]" pageId="5" pageNumber="192">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,454,764,789]" pageId="5" pageNumber="192">Habitat and ecology.</emphasis>
Females of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1862" box="[605,734,765,788]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="192" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="icterops">
<emphasis box="[605,734,765,788]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="192">H. icterops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were collected in small order streams (igarapés) inside the Amazon forest, hanging on leaves and branches, typical of other congeners. Males also hang from tree leaves over the stream; face-offs in territorial contests between males are a regular sight. Both males and females seem to be shade-seekers. Furthermore, at the sites of collection of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1862" box="[796,921,873,896]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="192" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="icterops">
<emphasis box="[796,921,873,896]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="192">H. icterops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, we found several specimens of 
<taxonomicName authority="Sjostedt, 1918" authorityName="Sjostedt" authorityYear="1918" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="192" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="silvarum">
<emphasis box="[1301,1436,871,896]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="192">H. silvarum</emphasis>
Sjöstedt, 1918
</taxonomicName>
, a widespread species of the Brazilian North, which belongs to Lencioni’s Group A.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
